# a7da69e6e261424890b796eaf18f92e6
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:22
msgid "TSHttpConnectWithPluginId"
msgstr ""

# 85a66f7af63b4aa99819b2d48301462b
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:24
msgid ""
"Allows the plugin to initiate an http connection. This will tag the HTTP "
"state machine with extra data that can be accessed by the logging "
"interface. The connection is treated as an HTTP transaction as if it came"
" from a client."
msgstr ""

# c8f451fe32284eb983baba3f05206bea
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:30
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

# 40946effcc8442a1af3469d6d54f93db
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:32
msgid "`#include <ts/ts.h>`"
msgstr ""

# 00619e4e6e014379b6d511a98ad9c47a
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:37
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

# 201104f9f80a4292b8188b3e17abe6af
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:39
msgid ""
"This call attempts to create an HTTP state machine and a virtual "
"connection to that state machine. This is more efficient than using "
":c:func:`TSNetConnect` because it avoids using the operating system stack"
" via the loopback interface."
msgstr ""

# c67264eabd484a86afb1a64b21249ba4
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:47
msgid ":arg:`addr`"
msgstr ""

# 95cf53b7b01848108ccc7708aa0a3d4b
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:45
msgid ""
"This is the network address of the target of the connection. This "
"includes the port which should be stored in the :c:type:`sockaddr` "
"structure pointed at by :arg:`addr`."
msgstr ""

# 766a7277c4bc4aa0a25fefc47032f5b7
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:55
msgid ":arg:`tag`"
msgstr ""

# 79cad1a91dd14d3986f805b0da95df78
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:50
msgid ""
"This is a tag that is passed through to the HTTP state machine. It must "
"be a persistent string that has a lifetime longer than the connection. It"
" is accessible via the log field :ref:`pitag <pitag>`. This is intended "
"as a class or type identifier that is consistent across all connections "
"for this plugin. In effect, the name of the plugin. This can be "
":literal:`NULL`."
msgstr ""

# 563b4e01e44744569217def84c9d515e
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:65
msgid ":arg:`id`"
msgstr ""

# 719f13a21d9344e284d6b9546d16637d
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:58
msgid ""
"This is a numeric identifier that is passed through to the HTTP state "
"machine. It is accessible via the log field :ref:`piid <piid>`. This is "
"intended as a connection identifier and should be distinct for every call"
" to :c:func:`TSHttpConnectWithPluginId`. The easiest mechanism is to "
"define a plugin global value and increment it for each connection. The "
"value :literal:`0` is reserved to mean \"not set\" and can be used as a "
"default if this functionality is not needed."
msgstr ""

# d2c4dc6966414e50b0d866deae33ead9
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:67
msgid ""
"The virtual connection returned as the :c:type:`TSCVonn` is API "
"equivalent to a network virtual connection both to the plugin and to "
"internal mechanisms. Data is read and written to the connection (and "
"thence to the target system) by reading and writing on this virtual "
"connection."
msgstr ""

# 57c35f04e6e649f198e71370fa46295f
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:75
msgid ""
"This function only opens the connection. To drive the transaction an "
"actual HTTP request must be sent and the HTTP response handled. The "
"transaction is handled as a standard HTTP transaction and all of the "
"standard configuration options and plugins will operate on it."
msgstr ""

# d401aa8fec90403096a265847c2344d8
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:80
msgid ""
"The combination of :arg:`tag` and :arg:`id` is intended to enable "
"correlation in log post processing. The :arg:`tag` identifies the "
"connection as related to the plugin and the :arg:`id` can be used in "
"conjuction with plugin generated logs to correlate the log records."
msgstr ""

# 7e374a5bcb5a47d182b4aec805afd478
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:86
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

# 9814bb8f84a94d389a9bc3bb3df85541
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpConnectWithPluginId.en.rst:88
msgid ""
"The SPDY implementation uses this to correlate client sessions with SPDY "
"streams. Each client connection is assigned a distinct numeric "
"identifier. This is passed as the :arg:`id` to "
":c:func:`TSHttpConnectWithPluginId`. The :arg:`tag` is selected to be the"
" NPN string for the client session protocol, e.g. \"spdy/3\" or "
"\"spdy/3.1\". Log post processing can then count the number of "
"connections for the various supported protocols and the number of SPDY "
"virtual streams for each real client connection to Traffic Server."
msgstr ""

